  "text": "The grafana/grafana repository contains both legacy and unified alerting implementations. Legacy alerting is defined in pkg/services/sqlstore/migrations/alert_mig.go, which creates and manages the legacy 'alert' table with columns for alert configuration including dashboard_id, panel_id, message, state, and handler. The unified alerting (ngalert) engine is implemented in pkg/services/ngalert/, with key components being: (1) AlertRule model in pkg/services/ngalert/models/alert_rule.go defining unified alert rule structure; (2) Alert rule storage in pkg/services/ngalert/store/alert_rule.go providing database operations for unified alert rules; (3) Alert rules provisioning service in pkg/services/ngalert/provisioning/alert_rules.go for managing rule lifecycle. The migration from legacy to unified alerting is implemented through multiple migration files in pkg/services/sqlstore/migrations/ualert/: (1) ualert.go contains the main migration logic including upgradeNgAlerting and updateDashboardUIDPanelIDMigration which converts legacy dashboard alerts to unified format; (2) tables.go defines schema for unified alerting tables; (3) org_upgrade_state_mig.go handles organization upgrade state tracking; (4) migration_service_migration.go tracks migration status. Legacy notification configuration storage is maintained in pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/legacy_storage/ for backward compatibility. The api/compat/compat.go file provides conversion functions between legacy and unified alert rule formats, with symbols like AlertRuleFromProvisionedAlertRule enabling interoperability. Migration annotations (MigratedContactLabelPrefix, MigratedAlertIdAnnotation) in alert_rule.go track alerts that have been migrated from legacy to unified format."
}

